<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ruin2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ruin,</orth> vb. to demolish, to destroy, to subvert; absol.: <bibl n="shak. son 125.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 125, 4</bibl> (<emph>--ing</emph> == ruin). <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.40" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 40</bibl>. Trans.: <bibl n="shak. ven 954" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 954</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 73.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 73, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.119.11" default="NO" valid="yes">119, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.4.45" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 4, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.2.37" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 2, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 2.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 1, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.382" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 382</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.382" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 382</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.2.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 2, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 2, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.137" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 51</bibl>. <emph>--ed</emph> == ruinous: <cit><quote>send the breath of parley into his --ed ears,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.34" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 34</bibl></cit>. Peculiar expression: <cit><quote>what ruins are in me that can be found, by him not --ed?</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 97</bibl></cit> (cf. <cit><quote>worth the want that you have wanted,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.282" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 282</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>our love, which, left unshown, is often left unloved,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.6.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 6, 52</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to mend the hurt that his unkindness marred,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 478" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 478</bibl></cit>. cf. <emph>honoured</emph> (Ff) in <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 81</bibl>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>